<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In the Programmer's Reference Guide (<a href="http://zendframework.com/manual/1.10/en/zend.controller.router.html">http://zendframework.com/manual/1.10/â€¦</a>) the lighttpd rewrite rule there is:</p>

<p><code>
url.rewrite-once = (
    ".<em>\?(.</em>)$" =&gt; "/index.php?$1",
    ".*.(js|ico|gif|jpg|png|css|html)$" =&gt; "$0",
    "" =&gt; "/index.php"
)
</code></p>

<p>Since 1.4.24, lighttpd adds a new configuration option that we can use to more closely emulate the Apache .htaccess behavior:</p>

<p><code>
url.rewrite-if-not-file = (
    "/(.*)$" =&gt; "/index.php?$1",
)
</code></p>

